<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="572" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,618,1077]" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,690,716]" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length of forewing 19. 
<quantity box="[588,657,691,717]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="572" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang &amp; Zhu &amp; Chen &amp; Xu &amp; Wang &amp; Fan &amp; Pan &amp; Espeland, 2022" authorityName="Huang &amp; Zhu &amp; Chen &amp; Xu &amp; Wang &amp; Fan &amp; Pan &amp; Espeland" authorityYear="2022" box="[667,869,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Agalope" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jianqingi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[667,869,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">Agalope jianqingi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[876,940,691,717]" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[876,940,691,717]" pageId="15" pageNumber="572" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler, 1875" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1875" box="[1141,1436,690,717]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Agalope" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="primularis">
<emphasis box="[1141,1290,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">A. primularis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Butler, A. G." box="[1297,1436,690,717]" pageId="15" pageNumber="572" pagination="391 - 393" refId="ref7367" refString="Butler, A. G. (1875) Descriptions of several new Species of Indian Heterocerous Lepidoptera. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1875, 391 - 393." type="journal article" year="1875">Butler, 1875</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,245,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–30" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1828,1852]" captionTargetBox="[242,1346,181,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[242,1346,181,1804]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 21–30. Adults of Agalope spp. 21, Agalope lucia, female, syntype, Tsekou, Yunnan (NHMUK), by courtesy of Dr. Mamoru Owada; 22, ditto, female, Gongshan, Yunnan (CHSY); 23, ditto, female, Gongshan, Yunnan, GSAG3 (CHSY); 24, ditto, male, Badi, Weixi, Yunnan, AG04 (CHSY); 25, ditto, male, Samage, Weixi, Yunnan, AG03 (SCAU); 26, A. dejeani, male, Jinchuan, Sichuan, JCAG2(CHSY); 27, ditto, JCAG1(CHSY); 28, A. bieti, male, HT, Kangding, Sichuan (NHMUK), by courtesy of Dr. K.A. Efetov; 29, A. jianqingi sp. n., male, HT, Pianma, Yunnan (CHSY); 30, A. primularis, male, Nepal, after Owada &amp; Horie (2000). Scale bar for figs 21–27, 29." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854086/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">Figs 30</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[256,326,726,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 51–56" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1592,1616]" captionTargetBox="[183,1421,189,1569]" captionTargetId="figure-20@11.[167,1421,181,1569]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 51–56. Male genitalia and 8th abdominal segment of Agalope spp. 51, Agalope lucia, slide AG03; 52, A. dejeani, slide JCAG1; 53, A. jianqingi sp. n., HT, slide PMAG1; 54, A. primularis, after Horie (1993); 55, 8th segment of A. jianqingi sp. n., slide PMAG1; 56, 8th tergite of A. primularis, after Horie (1993). Scale bar for figs 51–53, 55." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854102" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854102/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">54, 56</figureCitation>
) from Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[490,557,727,753]" name="Nepal" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and Northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[760,818,727,753]" name="India" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">India</collectingCountry>
for sharing a similar 8 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1067,1080,726,740]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">th</superScript>
tergite, which bears two narrow and slender processes, whereas in other congeners these processes are thick and stout or absent (
<bibRefCitation author="Owada, M." box="[1215,1362,763,789]" pageId="15" pageNumber="572" pagination="85 - 95" refId="ref7868" refString="Owada, M. (1992) The chalcosiine moths of Agalope (Lepidoptera, Zygaenidae) from Taiwan, with notes on allied genera. Japanese Journal of Entomology, Tokyo, 60, 85 - 95." type="journal article" year="1992">Owada 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Horie, K." pageId="15" pageNumber="572" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref7400" refString="Horie, K. (1993) Zygaenidae. In: Haruta, T. (Ed.), Moths of Nepal. Part 2. Japan Heterocerist's Society, Tokyo, pp. 1 - 4." type="book chapter" year="1993">Horie 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Owada, M. &amp; Horie, K." box="[222,465,799,825]" pageId="15" pageNumber="572" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref7907" refString="Owada, M. &amp; Horie, K. (2000) The genus Agalope (s. str.) (Zygaenidae, Chalcosiinae) from the Himalayas and the Indo-Chinese Peninsula. In: Haruta, T. (Ed.), Moths of Nepal. Part 6. Japan Heterocerist's Society, Tokyo, pp. 1 - 8, pl. 161." type="journal article" year="2000">Owada &amp; Horie 2000</bibRefCitation>
), but it can be immediately distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1875" box="[994,1142,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Agalope" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="primularis">
<emphasis box="[994,1142,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">A. primularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following characters: 1) male forewing ground color is creamy white instead of yellow in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1875" box="[1145,1293,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Agalope" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="primularis">
<emphasis box="[1145,1293,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">A. primularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 2) posterior tegumenal projection is much broader and longer; 3) notch between the lobes of juxta is wider and deeper; 4) valva is more slender, with the distal part longer and 5) aedeagus shorter and broader.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="572" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,618,1077]" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,942,968]" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from Pianma Town (
<figureCitation box="[691,775,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURES 62–67" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1875,1899]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-24@14.[151,1435,181,1851]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 62–67. Habitats and living adult of Agalope spp. in P.R. China. 62, Pianma, Lushui, Western Yunnan; 63, Samage, Weixi, Northwestern Yunnan; 64, Gongshan, Nujiang Lisu Autonomous Prefecture, Western Yunnan; 65, living adult of A. aurelia, resting on leaves, Gongshan; 66, Longgu Village, Chayu, Southeastern Xizang; 67, Taohuagou, Bomi, Southeastern Xizang." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854108/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
) located at the border of 
<collectingCountry box="[1070,1137,943,969]" name="China" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1196,1305,943,969]" name="Myanmar" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
in Western 
<collectingRegion box="[151,240,979,1005]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, P. R. 
<collectingCountry box="[310,381,979,1005]" name="China" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="572" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,618,1077]" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1015,1041]" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huang &amp; Zhu &amp; Chen &amp; Xu &amp; Wang &amp; Fan &amp; Pan &amp; Espeland" authorityYear="2022" box="[567,668,1015,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Agalope" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jianqingi">
<emphasis box="[567,668,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="572">jianqingi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is dedicated to the Chinese entomologist Mr. Jian-qing Zhu, a friend of the first author and an expert in the taxonomy of 
